article.headline: Dartmouth 56, Harvard 54
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- David Gardner scored six of Dartmouth's last eight points and led the Big Green to a 56-54 victory over Harvard on Saturday night in the Ivy League opener for both teams. Gardner had 11 of his 12 points in the second half and had three layups in a two-minute stretch late in the game. The first gave the Big Green a 50-49 lead with 3:41 to go, and Dartmouth (3-7, 1-0 Ivy) never trailed again. He scored on Dartmouth's next possession for a 52-49 advantage at 2:35. Then with 1:26 to play, Gardner got an offensive rebound of his own miss and followed with another layup for a 56-52 lead. Gardner also finished with a game-high nine rebounds. Kevin Rogus had 18 points for Harvard (1-12, 0-1) Leon Pattman had 11 of his team-high 16 points in the opening half when Dartmouth recovered from a 12-point deficit to take a 29-28 lead at the half.
